    "body": "## Steps to reproduce\r\n- On the homescreen, click the url bar to raise the keyboard\r\n- Lower the keyboard\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\nFocus logo and hint text moves smoothly into new position (like previous release)\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\nWhen keyboard is lowered, the hint text and the focus logo unexpectedly move upward a few pixels before animating downward. When the keyboard is raised, the hint text and focus logo unexpectedly move downward a few pixels before animating upward. This creates a \"bouncing\" effect.\r\n\r\nIt seems like the root cause might be because the 5 dots (for additional hint text?) is getting added to the layout during the animation, causing the existing elements to move into a new position.\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/759372/131590598-81896b04-9dec-4ec7-8296-1d1e14069c51.mp4\r\n\r\n### Device information\r\n\r\n* Android device: Moto G5\r\n* Focus version: local build based off of 56ab7b8a872f19f4397553b516837b80b750c6f1\r\n",
